</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289466/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="67" targetBox="[161,1425,199,1793]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1823,1999]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,331,1823,1845]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">FIGURES 11–14</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Condamin 1971" authorityName="Condamin" authorityYear="1971" box="[343,698,1823,1846]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bicyclus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maesseni">
<emphasis box="[343,528,1823,1846]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">Bicyclus maesseni</emphasis>
Condamin 1971
</taxonomicName>
. 11. Male, Ghana (OB–TER–0067). 12. Female, Ghana (ABRI–14–354). 13. Male genitalia, Ghana (OB–TER–0067). 14. Androconial structures (OB–TER–0067): There is a patch of androconial scales in the basal parts of space 1b on the dorsal forewing covered by a loose comb of black hairs (encircled in white). The basal parts of vein 1b on dorsal hindwing are enlarged into a small lightly coloured bulb, and this part of the vein is not covered by any long dark hairs. The enlarged part of the vein is shorter, but wider, than in 
<taxonomicName box="[1006,1124,1946,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bicyclus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignobilis">
<emphasis box="[1006,1124,1946,1968]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">B. ignobilis</emphasis>
